install cf cli
#### What?

The CF CLI will allow you to manage your applications, users and services in a CF environment

#### How?
Install the CLI from https://github.com/cloudfoundry/cli


#### Expected Result
```
$ cf version
cf version 6.22.1+6b7af9c-2016-09-24

$ cf help -a # To see all the commands
```
L: core tools
---
install PCF Dev
#### What?

PCF Dev is slimmed down Pivotal Cloud Foundry that is able to run on a developer machine. This is the quickest way to play with Cloud Foundry to test your applications in the cloud.

#### How?
1. You'll need a [Pivotal Network Account](https://network.pivotal.io)
1. Install PCF Dev from [https://pivotal.io/pcf-dev](https://pivotal.io/pcf-dev)

#### Expected Result
```
$ cf dev start
... booting ..
$ cf dev version
PCF Dev version 0.22.0 (CLI: e278885, OVA: 0.389.0)
$ cf dev target  #short for cf api ... && cf login
Successfully logged in to api.local.pcfdev.io as user.
```
L: core tools
